metadata.name: Snowed in
metadata.description:
The Rorbu, synonymous with the Lofoten Islands of Norway. The name comes from the Norwegian "Ro" translating to Rowing and "Bu" a small house to live or for storage. During the Winter months the heavy snows collect against the red timber and small windows of these little cabins. If I was to be snowed in anywhere this would be my choice.

Snowed in by Lee Pengelly

Edition: open edition

Location: Lofoten, Norway.
